==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Potto
<hw>Pot"to</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A nocturnal mammal (<spn>Perodictius potto</spn>) of
the Lemur family, found in West Africa. It has rudimentary forefingers.
Called also <altname>aposoro</altname>, and <altname>bush
dog</altname>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The kinkajou.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pott's disease</ent>⟦br⟧
